Package: CASSIA
Title: Collaborative Agent System for Single-Cell Interpretable Annotation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Elliot Yixuan", "Xie", email = "xie227@wisc.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides R wrappers for a collaborative agent system designed for
    single-cell RNA sequencing cell type annotation. Uses 'reticulate' to interface
    with a Python backend that leverages large language models for interpretable
    cell type analysis and batch processing of single-cell data.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/ElliotXie/CASSIA,
    https://docs.cassia.bio
BugReports: https://github.com/ElliotXie/CASSIA/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Depends:
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports:
    reticulate
Suggests:
    Seurat,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Config/reticulate:
    list(
        conda_env = "cassia_env"
    )
